table asyncio_extra127.asyncio_semaphore_class_and_methods:
  description: "asyncio.Semaphore class hierarchy and method __qualname__ checks in asynciolockident127 namespace — wave 255 theme: asyncio.Semaphore shares the same class hierarchy structure as asyncio.Lock; Semaphore.__name__.__eq__('Semaphore')==True (len=9: 'Semaphore'=9, five chars longer than 'Lock'=4); Semaphore.__module__.__eq__('asyncio.locks')==True (same module as Lock); Semaphore.__bases__[0].__name__.__eq__('_ContextManagerMixin')==True (same direct base as Lock); Semaphore.__mro__.__len__()==4 (MRO is [Semaphore, _ContextManagerMixin, _LoopBoundMixin, object]; identical structure to Lock's 4-element MRO); Semaphore.acquire.__qualname__.__eq__('Semaphore.acquire')==True (len=17: 'Semaphore.'=10+'acquire'=7=17; five chars longer than Lock.acquire at 12 because 'Semaphore.'=10 vs 'Lock.'=5); Semaphore.acquire.__qualname__.__len__()==17; Semaphore.release.__qualname__.__eq__('Semaphore.release')==True (len=17: 'Semaphore.'=10+'release'=7=17, tied with acquire); Semaphore.release.__qualname__.__len__()==17; Semaphore.locked.__qualname__.__eq__('Semaphore.locked')==True (len=16: 'Semaphore.'=10+'locked'=6=16); Semaphore.locked.__qualname__.__len__()==16; all methods are class='function' (pure-Python); verified with Python 3.14.3"
